list.item:
Patients should be advised not to use betamethasone dipropionate lotion (augmented) in the treatment of diaper dermatitis. Betamethasone dipropionate lotion (augmented) should not be applied in the diaper areas as diapers or plastic pants may constitute occlusive dressing (See 
                                 DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                              ).

text.paragraph:
Topically applied betamethasone dipropionate lotion (augmented) can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects (See 
                        PRECAUTIONS
                     ).
